#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:263
#, no-c-format
msgid "Apache Configuration Files"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: tertiary
#: apache2.xml:266
#, no-c-format
msgid "files"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:267
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section gives an overview of the Apache configuration files. If you use "
"&yast; for configuration, you do not need to touch these files&mdash;"
"however, the information might be useful for you if you want to switch to "
"manual configuration later on."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:273
#, no-c-format
msgid "Apache configuration files can be found in two different locations:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:289
#, no-c-format
msgid "/etc/sysconfig/apache2"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:290
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>/etc/sysconfig/apache2</filename> controls some global settings of "
"Apache, like modules to load, additional configuration files to include, "
"flags with which the server should be started, and flags that should be "
"added to the command line. Every configuration option in this file is "
"extensively documented and therefore not mentioned here. For a general-"
"purpose Web server, the settings in <filename>/etc/sysconfig/apache2</"
"filename> should be sufficient for any configuration needs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:302
#, no-c-format
msgid "/etc/apache2/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>/etc/apache2/</filename> hosts all configuration files for Apache. "
"In the following, the purpose of each file is explained. Each file includes "
"several configuration options (also called <emphasis>directives</emphasis>). "
"Every configuration option in these files is extensively documented and "
"therefore not mentioned here."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:310
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Apache configuration files are organized as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:313
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"/etc/apache2/\n"
"     |\n"
"     |- charset.conv\n"
"     |- conf.d/\n"
"     |   |\n"
"     |   |- *.conf\n"
"     |\n"
"     |- default-server.conf\n"
"     |- errors.conf\n"
"     |- httpd.conf\n"
"     |- listen.conf\n"
"     |- magic\n"
"     |- mime.types\n"
"     |- mod_*.conf\n"
"     |- server-tuning.conf\n"
"     |- ssl.*\n"
"     |- ssl-global.conf\n"
"     |- sysconfig.d\n"
"     |   |\n"
"     |   |- global.conf\n"
"     |   |- include.conf\n"
"     |   |- loadmodule.conf . .\n"
"     |\n"
"     |- uid.conf\n"
"     |- vhosts.d\n"
"     |   |- *.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:315
#, no-c-format
msgid "Apache Configuration Files in /etc/apache2/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:317
#, no-c-format
msgid "charset.conv"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:320
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies which character sets to use for different languages. Do not edit "
"this file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:327
#, no-c-format
msgid "conf.d/*.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:330
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configuration files added by other modules. These configuration files can be "
"included into your virtual host configuration where needed. See "
"<filename>vhosts.d/vhost.template</filename> for examples. By doing so, you "
"can provide different module sets for different virtual hosts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:339
#, no-c-format
msgid "default-server.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:342
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Global configuration for all virtual hosts with reasonable defaults. Instead "
"of changing the values, overwrite them with a virtual host configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:350
#, no-c-format
msgid "errors.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:353
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Defines how Apache responds to errors. To customize these messages for all "
"virtual hosts, edit this file. Otherwise overwrite these directives in your "
"virtual host configurations."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:361
#, no-c-format
msgid "httpd.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:364
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The main Apache server configuration file. Avoid changing this file. It "
"primarily contains include statements and global settings. Overwrite global "
"settings in the pertinent configuration files listed here. Change host-"
"specific settings (such as document root) in your virtual host configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:374
#, no-c-format
msgid "listen.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:377
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Binds Apache to specific IP addresses and ports. Name-based virtual hosting "
"is also configured here. For details, see <xref linkend=\"sec.apache2."
"configuration.manually.vhost.named_vhosts\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:385
#, no-c-format
msgid "magic"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:388
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Data for the mime_magic module that helps Apache automatically determine the "
"MIME type of an unknown file. Do not change this file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:395
#, no-c-format
msgid "mime.types"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:398
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"MIME types known by the system (this actually is a link to <filename>/etc/"
"mime.types</filename>). Do not edit this file. If you need to add MIME types "
"not listed here, add them to <filename>mod_mime-defaults.conf</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:407
#, no-c-format
msgid "mod_*.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:410
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configuration files for the modules that are installed by default. Refer to "
"<xref linkend=\"sec.apache2.modules\"/> for details. Note that configuration "
"files for optional modules reside in the directory <filename>conf.d</"
"filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:419
#, no-c-format
msgid "server-tuning.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:422
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Contains configuration directives for the different MPMs (see <xref linkend="
"\"sec.apache2.modules.mpm\"/>) and general configuration options that "
"control Apache's performance. Properly test your Web server when making "
"changes here."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: apache2.xml:431
#, no-c-format
msgid "<filename>ssl-global.conf</filename> and <filename>ssl.*</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:434
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Global SSL configuration and SSL certificate data. Refer to <xref linkend="
"\"sec.apache2.ssl\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:441
#, no-c-format
msgid "sysconfig.d/*.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:444
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configuration files automatically generated from <filename>/etc/sysconfig/"
"apache2</filename>. Do not change any of these files&mdash;edit <filename>/"
"etc/sysconfig/apache2</filename> instead. Do not put other configuration "
"files in this directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:453
#, no-c-format
msgid "uid.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:456
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specifies under which user and group ID Apache runs. Do not change this file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:463
#, no-c-format
msgid "vhosts.d/*.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:466
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Your virtual host configuration should be located here. The directory "
"contains template files for virtual hosts with and without SSL. Every file "
"in this directory ending with <filename>.conf</filename> is automatically "
"included in the Apache configuration. Refer to <xref linkend=\"sec.apache2."
"configuration.manually.vhost\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

