msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1573
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Apache can be extended by advanced users by writing custom modules. To "
"develop modules for Apache or compile third-party modules, the package "
"<systemitem>apache2-devel</systemitem> is required along with the "
"corresponding development tools. <systemitem>apache2-devel</systemitem> also "
"contains the <command>apxs2</command> tools, which are necessary for "
"compiling additional modules for Apache."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1581
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>apxs2</command> enables the compilation and installation of modules "
"from source code (including the required changes to the configuration "
"files), which creates <emphasis>dynamic shared objects</emphasis> (DSOs) "
"that can be loaded into Apache at runtime."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1587
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>apxs2</command> binaries are located under <filename>/usr/sbin</"
"filename>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1593
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>/usr/sbin/apxs2</filename>&mdash;suitable for building an "
"extension module that works with any MPM. The installation location is "
"<filename>/usr/lib64/apache2</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1600
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>/usr/sbin/apxs2-prefork</filename>&mdash;suitable for prefork MPM "
"modules. The installation location is <filename>/usr/lib64/apache2-prefork</"
"filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1607
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<filename>/usr/sbin/apxs2-worker</filename>&mdash;suitable for worker MPM "
"modules. The installation location is <filename>/usr/lib64/apache2-worker</"
"filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1614
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Install and activate a module from source code with the following commands:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:1617
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"cd /path/to/module/source\n"
"apxs2 -cia <replaceable>mod_foo</replaceable>.c"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1618
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"where <option>-c</option> compiles the module, <option>-i</option> installs "
"it, and <option>-a</option> activates it. Other options of <command>apxs2</"
"command> are described in the <systemitem>apxs2(1)</systemitem> man page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1627
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling CGI Scripts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: secondary
#: apache2.xml:1631
#, no-c-format
msgid "CGI scripts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1633
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Apache's Common Gateway Interface (CGI) lets you create dynamic content with "
"programs or scripts usually called CGI scripts. CGI scripts can be written "
"in any programming language. Usually, script languages such as Perl or PHP "
"are used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1640
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To enable Apache to deliver content created by CGI scripts, "
"<systemitem>mod_cgi</systemitem> needs to be activated. "
"<systemitem>mod_alias</systemitem> is also needed. Both modules are enabled "
"by default. Refer to <xref linkend=\"sec.apache2.modules.activating\"/> for "
"details on activating modules."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1649
#, no-c-format
msgid "CGI Security"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1650
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Allowing the server to execute CGI scripts is a potential security hole. "
"Refer to <xref linkend=\"sec.apache2.security\"/> for additional information."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1657
#, no-c-format
msgid "Apache Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1658
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &productname;, the execution of CGI scripts is only allowed in the "
"directory <filename>/srv/www/cgi-bin/</filename>. This location is already "
"configured to execute CGI scripts. If you have created a virtual host "
"configuration (see <xref linkend=\"sec.apache2.configuration.manually.vhost"
"\"/>) and want to place your scripts in a host-specific directory, you must "
"unlock and configure this directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1668
#, no-c-format
msgid "VirtualHost CGI Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:1669
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"ScriptAlias /cgi-bin/ \"/srv/www/&wwwname;/cgi-bin/\"<co xml:id=\"co.apache2."
"cgi.script_alias\"/>\n"
"\n"
"&lt;Directory \"/srv/www/&wwwname;/cgi-bin/\"&gt;\n"
" Options +ExecCGI<co xml:id=\"co.apache2.cgi.options\"/>\n"
" AddHandler cgi-script .cgi .pl<co xml:id=\"co.apache2.cgi.handler\"/>\n"
" Require all granted<co xml:id=\"co.apache2.cgi.order\"/>\n"
"&lt;/Directory&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1672
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tells Apache to handle all files within this directory as CGI scripts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1677
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enables CGI script execution"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1682
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Tells the server to treat files with the extensions .pl and .cgi as CGI "
"scripts. Adjust according to your needs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1688
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <systemitem>Require</systemitem> directive controls the default access "
"state. In this case, access is granted to the specified directory without "
"limitation. For more information on authentication and authorization, see "
"<link xlink:href=\"http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/howto/auth.html\"></"
"link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1701
#, no-c-format
msgid "Running an Example Script"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1702
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"CGI programming differs from \"regular\" programming in that the CGI "
"programs and scripts must be preceded by a MIME-Type header such as "
"<literal>Content-type: text/html</literal>. This header is sent to the "
"client, so it understands what kind of content it receives. Secondly, the "
"script's output must be something the client, usually a Web browser, "
"understands&mdash;HTML usually, or plain text or images, for example."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1710
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A simple test script available under <filename>/usr/share/doc/packages/"
"apache2/test-cgi</filename> is part of the Apache package. It outputs the "
"content of some environment variables as plain text. Copy this script to "
"either <filename>/srv/www/cgi-bin/</filename> or the script directory of "
"your virtual host (<filename>/srv/www/&wwwname;/cgi-bin/</filename>) and "
"name it <filename>test.cgi</filename>. Edit the file to have <literal>#!/bin/"
"sh</literal> as the first line."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1720
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Files accessible by the Web server should be owned by the user <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>. For additional information see <xref "
"linkend=\"sec.apache2.security\"/>. Because the Web server runs with a "
"different user, the CGI scripts must be world-executable and world-readable. "
"Change into the CGI directory and use the command <command>chmod 755 test."
"cgi</command> to apply the proper permissions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1728
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now call <literal>http://localhost/cgi-bin/test.cgi</literal> or "
"<literal>http://&wwwname;/cgi-bin/test.cgi</literal>. You should see the "
"<quote>CGI/1.0 test script report</quote>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1736 apache2.xml:1742
#, no-c-format
msgid "CGI Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1737
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you do not see the output of the test program but an error message "
"instead, check the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1750
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have configured your custom CGI directory, is it configured properly? "
"If in doubt, try the script within the default CGI directory <filename>/srv/"
"www/cgi-bin/</filename> and call it with <literal>http://localhost/cgi-bin/"
"test.cgi</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1758
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Are the file permissions correct? Change into the CGI directory and execute "
"<command>ls -l test.cgi</command>. Its output should start with"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:1762
#, no-c-format
msgid "-rwxr-xr-x  1 root root"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1765
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that the script does not contain programming errors. If you have "
"not changed <filename>test.cgi</filename>, this should not be the case, but "
"if you are using your own programs, always make sure that they do not "
"contain programming errors."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1776
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting Up a Secure Web Server with SSL"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: secondary
#: apache2.xml:1780 apache2.xml:1818 apache2.xml:2063
#, no-c-format
msgid "<secondary>SSL</secondary>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1782
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whenever sensitive data, such as credit card information, is transferred "
"between Web server and client, it is desirable to have a secure, encrypted "
"connection with authentication. <systemitem>mod_ssl</systemitem> provides "
"strong encryption using the secure sockets layer (SSL) and transport layer "
"security (TLS) protocols for HTTP communication between a client and the Web "
"server. Using SSL/TLS, a private connection between Web server and client is "
"established. Data integrity is ensured and client and server can "
"authenticate each other."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1793
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For this purpose, the server sends an SSL certificate that holds information "
"proving the server's valid identity before any request to a URL is answered. "
"In turn, this guarantees that the server is the uniquely correct end point "
"for the communication. Additionally, the certificate generates an encrypted "
"connection between client and server that can transport information without "
"the risk of exposing sensitive, plain-text content."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1802
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<systemitem>mod_ssl</systemitem> does not implement the SSL/TLS protocols "
"itself, but acts as an interface between Apache and an SSL library. In "
"&productname;, the OpenSSL library is used. OpenSSL is automatically "
"installed with Apache."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1809
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The most visible effect of using <systemitem>mod_ssl</systemitem> with "
"Apache is that URLs are prefixed with <literal>https://</literal> instead of "
"<literal>http://</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1816
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating an SSL Certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: tertiary
#: apache2.xml:1819
#, no-c-format
msgid "creating an SSL certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1820
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use SSL/TLS with the Web server, you need to create an SSL certificate. "
"This certificate is needed for the authorization between Web server and "
"client, so that each party can clearly identify the other party. To ensure "
"the integrity of the certificate, it must be signed by a party every user "
"trusts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1827
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are three types of certificates you can create: a <quote>dummy</quote> "
"certificate for testing purposes only, a self-signed certificate for a "
"defined circle of users that trust you, and a certificate signed by an "
"independent, publicly-known certificate authority (CA)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1833
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Creating a certificate is a two step process. First, a private key for the "
"certificate authority is generated then the server certificate is signed "
"with this key."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1839 apache2.xml:2588
#, no-c-format
msgid "For More Information"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1840
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To learn more about concepts and definitions of SSL/TLS, refer to <link "
"xlink:href=\"http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/ssl/ssl_intro.html\">http://"
"httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/ssl/ssl_intro.html</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1846
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a <quote>Dummy</quote> Certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1847
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To generate a dummy certificate, call the script <command>/usr/bin/"
"gensslcert</command>. It creates or overwrites the files listed below. Use "
"<command>gensslcert</command>'s optional switches to fine-tune the "
"certificate. Call <command>/usr/bin/gensslcert </command> <option>-h</"
"option> for more information."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:1857
#, no-c-format
msgid "/etc/apache2/ssl.crt/ca.crt"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:1862
#, no-c-format
msgid "/etc/apache2/ssl.crt/server.crt"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:1867
#, no-c-format
msgid "/etc/apache2/ssl.key/server.key"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: filename
#: apache2.xml:1872
#, no-c-format
msgid "/etc/apache2/ssl.csr/server.csr"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1876
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A copy of <filename>ca.crt</filename> is also placed at <filename>/srv/www/"
"htdocs/CA.crt</filename> for download."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1881
#, no-c-format
msgid "For Testing Purposes Only"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1882
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A dummy certificate should never be used on a production system. Only use it "
"for testing purposes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1889
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a Self-Signed Certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1890
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you are setting up a secure Web server for an intranet or for a defined "
"circle of users, it is probably sufficient if you sign a certificate with "
"your own certificate authority (CA). Note that the visitors to such a site "
"will see the annoying \"this is an untrusted site\" warning because Web "
"browsers do not know the self-signed certificate."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1898
#, no-c-format
msgid "Self-Signed Certificates"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1899
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only use a self-signed certificate on a Web server that is accessed by "
"people who know and trust you as a certificate authority. It is not "
"recommended to use such a certificate for a public shop, for example."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1905
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First you need to generate a certificate signing request (CSR). You are "
"going to use <command>openssl</command>, with <literal>PEM</literal> as the "
"certificate format. During this step, you will be asked for a passphrase, "
"and to answer several questions. Remember the passphrase you enter as you "
"will need it in the future."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:1912
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"sudo openssl req -new &gt; new.cert.csr\n"
"Generating a 1024 bit RSA private key\n"
"..++++++\n"
".........++++++\n"
"writing new private key to 'privkey.pem'\n"
"Enter PEM pass phrase:<co xml:id=\"co.ssl.self.pass1\"/>\n"
"Verifying - Enter PEM pass phrase:<co xml:id=\"co.ssl.self.pass2\"/>\n"
"-----\n"
"You are about to be asked to enter information that will be incorporated\n"
"into your certificate request.\n"
"What you are about to enter is what is called a Distinguished Name or a DN.\n"
"There are quite a few fields but you can leave some blank\n"
"For some fields there will be a default value,\n"
"If you enter '.', the field will be left blank.\n"
"-----\n"
"Country Name (2 letter code) [AU]:<co xml:id=\"co.ssl.self.country\"/>\n"
"State or Province Name (full name) [Some-State]:<co xml:id=\"co.ssl.self."
"state\"/>\n"
"Locality Name (eg, city) []:<co xml:id=\"co.ssl.self.city\"/>\n"
"Organization Name (eg, company) [Internet Widgits Pty Ltd]:<co xml:id=\"co."
"ssl.self.org\"/>\n"
"Organizational Unit Name (eg, section) []:<co xml:id=\"co.ssl.self.uname\"/"
">\n"
"Common Name (for example server FQDN, or YOUR name) []:<co xml:id=\"co.ssl."
"self.cname\"/>\n"
"Email Address []:<co xml:id=\"co.ssl.self.email\"/>\n"
"\n"
"Please enter the following 'extra' attributes\n"
"to be sent with your certificate request\n"
"A challenge password []:<co xml:id=\"co.ssl.self.challenge\"/>\n"
"An optional company name []:<co xml:id=\"co.ssl.self.optional\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1915
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in your passphrase,"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1920
#, no-c-format
msgid "...fill it in once more (and remember it)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1925
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Fill in your 2 letter country code, such as <literal>GB</literal> or "
"<literal>CZ</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1931
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in the name of the state where you live."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1936
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in the city name, such as <literal>Prague</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1941
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in the name of the organization you work for."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1946
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in your organization unit, or leave blank if you have none."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1951
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Fill in either the domain name of the server, or your first and last name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1957
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in your work e-mail address."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1962
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Leave the challenge password empty, otherwise you will need to enter it "
"every time you restart the Apache Web server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1968
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill in the optional company name, or leave blank."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1973
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you can generate the certificate. You are going to use <command>openssl</"
"command> again, and the format of the certificate is the default "
"<literal>PEM</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:1979
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generating the Certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1981
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Export the private part of the key to <filename>new.cert.key</filename>. You "
"will be prompted for the passphrase you entered when creating the "
"certificate signing request (CSR)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:1986
#, no-c-format
msgid "sudo openssl rsa -in privkey.pem -out new.cert.key"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1989
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Generate the public part of the certificate according to the information you "
"filled out in the signing request. The <option>-days</option> option "
"specifies the length of time before the certificate expires. You can revoke "
"a certificate, or replace one before it expires."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:1995
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"sudo openssl x509 -in new.cert.csr -out new.cert.cert -req \\\n"
"-signkey new.cert.key -days 365"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1998
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Copy the certificate files to the relevant directories, so that the Apache "
"server can read them. Make sure that the private key <filename>/etc/apache2/"
"ssl.key/server.key</filename> is not world-readable, while the public PEM "
"certificate <filename>/etc/apache2/ssl.crt/server.crt</filename> is."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:2005
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"sudo cp new.cert.cert /etc/apache2/ssl.crt/server.crt\n"
"sudo cp new.cert.key /etc/apache2/ssl.key/server.key"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:2009
#, no-c-format
msgid "Public Certificate Location"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2010
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The last step is to copy the public certificate file from <filename>/etc/"
"apache2/ssl.crt/server.crt</filename> to a location where your users can "
"access it to incorporate it into the list of known and trusted CAs in their "
"Web browsers. Otherwise a browser complains that the certificate was issued "
"by an unknown authority."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:2020
#, no-c-format
msgid "Getting an Officially Signed Certificate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2021
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are several official certificate authorities that sign your "
"certificates. The certificate is signed by a trustworthy third party, so can "
"be fully trusted. Publicly operating secure Web servers usually have an "
"officially signed certificate. A list of the most used Certificate "
"Authorities (CAs) is available at <link xlink:href=\"https://en.wikipedia."
"org/wiki/Certificate_authority#Providers\"></link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2028
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When requesting an officially signed certificate, you do not send a "
"certificate to the CA. Instead, issue a Certificate Signing Request (CSR). "
"To create a CSR, run the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apache2.xml:2040
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"openssl req -new -newkey rsa:2048 -nodes -keyout newkey.pem -out newreq.pem"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2041
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You are asked to enter a distinguished name. This requires you to answer a "
"few questions, such as country name or organization name. Enter valid "
"data&mdash;everything you enter here later shows up in the certificate and "
"is checked. You do not need to answer every question. If one does not apply "
"to you or you want to leave it blank, use <quote>.</quote>. Common name is "
"the name of the CA itself&mdash;choose a significant name, such as "
"<replaceable>My company</replaceable> CA. Last, a challenge password and an "
"alternative company name must be entered."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2053
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Find the CSR in the directory from which you called the script. The file is "
"named <filename>newreq.pem</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:2061
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring Apache with SSL"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: tertiary
#: apache2.xml:2064
#, no-c-format
msgid "configure Apache with SSL"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2065
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The default port for SSL and TLS requests on the Web server side is 443. "
"There is no conflict between a <quote>regular</quote> Apache listening on "
"port 80 and an SSL/TLS-enabled Apache listening on port 443. In fact, HTTP "
"and HTTPS can be run with the same Apache instance. Usually separate virtual "
"hosts are used to dispatch requests to port 80 and port 443 to separate "
"virtual servers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apache2.xml:2074
#, no-c-format
msgid "Firewall Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2075
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Do not forget to open the firewall for SSL-enabled Apache on port 443. This "
"can be done with &yast; as described in <xref linkend=\"sec.security."
"firewall.SuSE.yast\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2081
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The SSL module is enabled by default in the global server configuration. In "
"case it has been disabled on your host, activate it with the following "
"command: <command>a2enmod ssl</command>. To finally enable SSL, the server "
"needs to be started with the flag <quote>SSL</quote>. To do so, call "
"<command>a2enflag SSL</command> (case-sensitive!). If you have chosen to "
"encrypt your server certificate with a password, you should also increase "
"the value for <systemitem>APACHE_TIMEOUT</systemitem> in <filename>/etc/"
"sysconfig/apache2</filename>, so you have enough time to enter the "
"passphrase when Apache starts. Restart the server to make these changes "
"active. A reload is not sufficient."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2093
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The virtual host configuration directory contains a template <filename>/etc/"
"apache2/vhosts.d/vhost-ssl.template</filename> with SSL-specific directives "
"that are extensively documented. Refer to <xref linkend=\"sec.apache2."
"configuration.manually.vhost\"/> for the general virtual host configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:2100
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To get started, copy the template to <filename>/etc/apache2/vhosts.d/"
"<replaceable>mySSL-host</replaceable>.conf</filename> and edit it. Adjusting "
"the values for the following directives should be sufficient:"
msgstr ""

